commentAnnotations.text: Janssen Research & Development is a global organization that operates through different legal entities in various countries. The legal entity acting as the sponsor may vary.
Vital sign assessments should be recorded in source documents but will not be routinely collected in the eCRF.
Blood samples for the assessment of CR MRD will no longer be collected except in subjects whose first assessment of CR is after the issue date of this amendment.

Review of systems should include inquiry of ocular symptoms (eg, dry eye, blurred vision). Subjects should be referred to an ophthalmologist for formal examination if Grade >= 2 symptoms are reported.

studyDefinitionDocumentVersions.description: Update safety information regarding cerebrovascular accidents and clarify vital sign monitoring.
Halt collection of CR MRD samples for specific subjects.
Clarify DMC recommendations and update hepatic impairment dose modifications.
Initial release of the clinical protocol.
